  m_overrideMarkdownText: '# Safe Dials


    ![alt text](../Documentation/Images/Safe.gif){style="width:50%;height:50%"}


    There
    is no off-the-shelf solution for using a single finger to swipe through safe
    numbers naturally. The <a href="./Assets/CrypticCabinet/Scripts/Puzzles/Safe/SwipeDetector.cs">final
    implementation</a> uses a trigger collider on the user''s index finger to detect
    swipes. When a swipe is detected, the number carousel animates up or down. Once
    all dials read the correct values, the safe door opens.


    ![alt text](../Documentation/Images/DialColliders.png){style="width:50%;height:50%"}



